label normal_ending:
    stop music
    hide bg lobby
    show bg_generic
    "Today is the day."
    "You've been cleaning for a while."
    "Planet Lele is clean enough, you say."
    "Arce doesn't look that convinced."
    show arce normal at truecenter
    arce "I don't know, [mcName]..."
    arce "I mean, it does look a little bit more lively. But i thought that this time the planet would be overflowing with spring."
    arce "HQ would probably agree with you, though."
    arce "..."
    show arce sad
    arce "I mean, we're still young. Sure we could spend a couple hundreds of years cleaning this planet."
    extend "...Right?"
    arce "..."
    show arce normal
    arce "You don't seem too convinced."
    arce "I guess in these last day we truly did achieved somethng."
    arce "And at least the Zababuglovers didn't eat all of our progress yet."
    arce "So, soon, they'll all be gone in search of another planet to destroy."
    arce "Hey, [mcName]."
    arce "We've been chasing the Zababuglovers all around the galaxy for centuries."
    arce "When we came to this planet, loooooong ago, the planet seemed dry."
    show arce sad
    extend "But, does it really feel like spring now?"
    menu:
        "Yes, this is enough":
            show arce normal
            arce "If you say so..."
            arce "Surely the HQ will call us soon to go to the next planet."
            hide arce
            "It didn't felt quite like spring today, you think."
            "But arce was right."
            "This were your first hundreds of years spent on Planet Lele, your first mission ever on the Spriggo Cleaning Brigade."
            "Soon, you will leave this planet and all you achieved on it."
            "You made sure to clean all the mess the Zababuglovers did."
            "At least that's something."
        "No, it doesn't":
            hide arce
            "You cold feel it in your supergalactic bones."
            "This wasn't enough."
            "You had seen it a lot of times before."
            "They had show you pictures of the so called Spring Planets the spriggos had been before."
            "By they never seemed like true spring to you."
            "Just by looking at Arce, you can feel he's troubled by this too."
            "Before you can say something to him, your intergalactic flykie-talkie starts buzzing."
            "Zababuglovers have been seen on a new planet and HQ wants you to go there."
            "Maybe some spriggos are not so interested on a true spring after all."
    


